{
  "texts": [
    "Crucially, these authors offer advice for teaching CAIL through metaphors, which we foreground in our work, suggesting that educators could ask students to share metaphors that they have discovered, and then challenge them to come up with additional input to extend or offer a new metaphor to deepen their understanding of these complex concepts.",
    "Journal of Interactive Media in Education DOI: 10.5334/jime.961",
    "To demonstrate the ways in which CAIL can be fostered by using metaphor, we opted to engage in a rigorous, reflexive, and creative investigation to develop a potential approach.",
    "We aimed firstly to identify appropriate metaphors and then create sample learning activities which are firmly embedded in existing frameworks for guiding AI competency development in education.",
    "Consequently, we selected the UNESCO AI competency framework for students (Miao et al. 2024) to underpin our learning activity development."
  ]
}